      "content": "that's a great start, really hits the tone i need. but for a college paper, i need to anticipate the pushback. people usually argue that meritocracy is a more fair way to distribute wealth and that redistribution is basically just punishing success. can you help me write a section that addresses those arguments but effectively shows why the meritocracy argument is actually just a way to ignore the reality of systemic racism?",
